column12: COMPOSITIONS AND METHODS FOR TARGETING TUMOR-ASSOCIATED MACROPHAGES
column13: The present invention relates to compounds that target monocytes, macrophages and other cells (such as dendritic cells) that express CD-206, particularly those cells at are assembled at a site of disease, using a target moiety coupled to a glucan backbone. The compounds disclosed here preferably comprise a glucan backbone, a targeting moiety, a targeting moiety linker, a payload and optionally a payload linker. The present invention also provides methods of making such compounds and compositions. The present invention also provides diagnostic methods and methods of treatment using compounds comprising a target moiety coupled to a glucan backbone.

column12: 종양-관련 대식세포 표적화용 조성물 및 방법
column13: 본 발명은 단핵구, 대식세포 및 CD-206을 발현하는 다른 세포(예컨대 수지상 세포), 특히 글루칸 백본에 커플링된 표적 모이어티를 사용한, 질환 부위에서 모이는 세포를 표적화하는 화합물에 관한 것이다. 본원에 개시된 화합물은 바람직하게는 글루칸 백본, 표적화 모이어티, 표적화 모이어티 링커, 페이로드 및 임의로 페이로드 링커를 포함한다. 본 발명은 또한 이러한 화합물 및 조성물을 제조하는 방법을 제공한다. 본 발명은 또한 글루칸 백본에 커플링된 표적 모이어티를 포함하는 화합물을 사용하는 진단 방법 및 치료 방법을 제공한다.

column12: USE OF MYELOID-LIKE PROGENITOR CELL POPULATIONS TO TREAT TUMORS
column13: This invention provides methods for treating tumors. The methods involve injecting or implanting a population of myeloid-like progenitor cells (e.g., human CD14 + cells or CD33 HI monocytes) to a subject afflicted with a tumor. The isolated cells can be further engineered to express an anti-tumor agent, e.g., an anti-angiogenic agent or a cytotoxic agent.

column13: An interconnect system includes various anti-backout latches that are movable between an engaged position and a disengaged position. When in the engaged position, the anti-backout latches can be configured to prevent an interconnect module, such as an optical transceiver, from becoming unmated from a host module. When in the disengaged position, the anti-backout latches permit the interconnect module to become unmated from a host module. Securement members are also disclosed that secure a heat sink to a module housing of the interconnect module.

column13: A cable connector system includes a cable including a center conductor and a housing supporting a portion of the center conductor.
